Like Doc Del, there was no reason for me to come home.  Hell, I was having the greatest adventure of all time! Oh sure, I missed sidewalks, round eyed women.  But what the hell, I was 19 years old and an E-5 and a section chief.  I had it made no guard duty, no k.p., no drill. <br>
Yes, the field activity, the red mud, the motar attacks, the rockets, the forward fire base activity.  That was all there.  But I was 19 and immortal!!<br>
There was nothing to come home to.  Dysfunctional family.  Yes they cared, yes they loved me and were concerned.  But it was not a reason for me to come home.  Those were issues that I had to process later.<br>
P.S. The only thing that stopped me from re-upping was the fact that I started seeing the other &quot;lifers&quot; from my first tour back in country. That and the fact that in a stupid attempt to &quot;bring discipline to the rank&quot; they started pulling field inspections, checking for polish on the boots(A little tough in the monsson season), and other b.s. like that.  Hell, I could have been an E-6 with choice of duty stations,(RIGHT) and a 15k re-up bonus.  No Thanks!   
